parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delamination of the fuel tank liner can cause fuel system clogs, leading to loss of power, engine stalling, and potential safety hazards.
The failure of the EGR, FICM, and injectors can cause traffic hazards, engine stalling, and loss of power, leading to potential safety risks.
The sudden stalling or shutdown of the engine can cause loss of control, leading to accidents, especially when driving on hills or curves.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off suddenly
especially when going down hills or making turns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty fuel injectors can cause engine misfires, stalling, and loss of power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Turbocharger failure can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and excessive fuel consumption, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
Oil leaks and contamination can cause engine damage, overheating, and failure, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
